<TEXT>
an agriculture department official rejected a 
call by the national academy of sciences for an overhaul of the 
nations critically important agricultural seed collection system 
the academy found that nearly half the seed samples in the 
nations principal collection are in danger and that only a new 
centralized administration can correct the deficiencies that led to 
that 
we think the system has worked very very well countered 
edward knipling deputy administrator of the usdas agricultural 
research service 
he said tuesday he didnt think stronger centralized management 
of the nations scattered seed banks and seed laboratories was 
possible 
the genes contained in the 232210 samples in the national seed 
storage laboratory in fort collins colo the nations largest 
collection have been used to develop new varieties of corn wheat 
and other important crops 
those new varieties have contributed to the tripling of corn 
yields and other huge gains in american agricultural productivity 
in recent decades the study said 
those gains have in turn boosted the nations economy cash 
receipts from us crops were 726 billion in 1988 up 107 
billion from the year before the study said 
managing genetic resources therefore is a strategic 
necessity for the united states the academy study said 
but the study found that 45 percent of the seed samples in the 
national seed storage laboratory contained fewer than 550 seeds 
that means they are in danger of vanishing as the seeds age and 
die 
such samples may contain irreplaceable genetic traits but the 
laboratory does not have the resources to regenerate those samples 
or increase their size by growing them to produce more seeds the 
study said 
regeneration of these samples is urgently needed the study 
said 
many of the studys conclusions echo the findings of a series 
last year by the associated press that concluded that thousands of 
irreplaceable crop seeds are dead or dying in an antiquated 
underfunded federal seed bank 
peter day of rutgers university in new jersey chairman of the 
academy committee that conducted the study said that henry l 
shands who heads the national plant germplasm system is 
extremely capable but appears to have little or no authority 
he has to depend on the agreement of large numbers of other 
committees in order to get anything done day said its a very 
difficult situation 
shands of the agricultural research service in beltsville md 
was traveling tuesday and could not be reached for comment 
genetic materials used in breeding are referred to as 
germplasm 
the national seed storage laboratory is the cornerstone of a 
network of perhaps 20 seed collections and laboratories around the 
country without a central administration the report said 
the great strategic importance of plant genetic resources 
requires that the system be administered centrally at the national 
level the study said 
the study said it will be very difficult if not impossible 
for the system to function properly without a major overhaul in its 
structure and administrative procedures 
other recommendations in the study included the appropriation of 
more money to regenerate seeds and the expansion of the national 
seed storage laboratory 
