gay and arab they are two words rarely spoken 
in the same breath and almost never in the conservative middle 
east but ramzi zakharia hopes to change that 
a year ago zakharia founded the gay and lesbian arabic society 
and discovered other arabamericans in the homosexual community who 
wanted to define a distinct gay arabic identity 
the result was very positive a lot of people wrote well 
its about time zakharia says 
zakharia rented a post office box started a newsletter and 
began to hold monthly meetings at peoples houses around 
washington today there are chapters in san francisco detroit 
los angeles and new york as well as a scattering of contacts in 
middle eastern countries including lebanon morocco egypt and 
yemen 
zakharia estimates total membership at about 400 and says gay 
arabs in london and paris are talking about organizing chapters as 
well 
