meeting here as scores of experts study the soviet economy in 
preparation for the soviet unions expected accession to the bank 
group 
the supreme soviet in moscow voted monday to abandon 70 years of 
communist economics and move toward a market economy in what some 
delegates at the annual meetings termed a second russian 
revolution 
treasury secretary nicholas brady told fellow bank governors 
monday that the international lending agencies must adjust their 
operations to emphasize development of the private sector rather 
than strengthening of government enterprises 
but gustavson said the actual privatization process would 
require experimentation we do not have a cookbook solution to 
reversing the balance from 90 percent state ownership and 10 
percent private to 1090 he said 
nations until recently under communist rule want to privatize 
but theres an underlying sensitivity about the disquieting 
prospect of selling out cheaply to foreign investors said 
