since iraq invaded kuwait on aug 2 the 
security council has passed nine resolutions condemning baghdad 
aug 3 the security council voted 140 to condemn the invasion 
and demand the immediate and unconditional withdrawal of iraqs 
troops yemen the only arab member of the council abstained on 
resolution 660 
aug 6 the council voted 130 to order a trade and financial 
embargo of iraq and occupied kuwait cuba and yemen abstained on 
resolution 661 
aug 9 the council voted 150 to declare iraqs annexation of 
kuwait null and void in international law in resolution 662 
aug 18 the council voted 150 to demand that iraq free all 
detained foreigners in resolution 664 
aug 25 the council voted 130 to give the united states and 
other naval powers the right to enforce the economic embargo 
against iraq and kuwait by halting their shipping cuba and yemen 
abstained on resolution 665 
sept 13 the council voted 132 to allow humanitarian food aid 
