but the wilson spokesman bill livingstone wouldnt commit the 
candidate to the voluntary limit a feinstein spokeswoman dee dee 
myers said the ruling may give feinstein a chance to chip away at 
wilsons fundraising lead 
if a law is overturned i dont know that we will feel 
compelled to abide by it she said 
us district judge lawrence karlton ruled tuesday that the 
limits unfairly help incumbents the limits affect campaigns for 
governor other statewide offices and some local posts 
two state legislators who cosponsored the limits said they 
would appeal the decision the state fair political practices 
commission a political watchdog agency said it would ask karlton 
to stay his ruling 
commission chairman john larson warned candidates not to start a 
fundraising frenzy 
karltons ruling invalidated proposition 73 which among other 
things limits individuals to a maximum of 1000 in contributions 
to a particular candidate per fiscal year the measure also limits 
political action committees donations to 2500 or 5000 per 
candidate per fiscal year depending on the size of the committee 
the limits are based on fiscal years that start on july 1 since 
state campaigns typically span two calendar years the measure 
creates three contribution periods an individual can give a 
candidate 3000 over two calendar years 
the judge said that helps incumbents because they usually start 
fundraising earlier than challengers do 
two of proposition 73s three authors assembly republican 
leader ross johnson and independent state sen quentin kopp said 
they would ask the 9th us circuit court of appeals to overturn 
karltons ruling 
the timing of this decision is most unfortunate johnson 
said 
former gov jerry brown chairman of the state democratic party 
one of the plaintiffs in the case said the decision strikes down 
one of the most pernicious campaign laws ever enacted and puts an 
end to the pervasive state censorship of grassroots activism 
imposed by proposition 73 
wilson had nearly 4 million at the start of the general 
election campaign in july feinstein had 645000 spokesmen for 
both candidates said they didnt know how much had been raised 
since july 
</TEXT>
