ceasefire 
the report said hun sen made the comments in a speech to a 
mass meeting in front of phnom penhs former royal palace 
his vietnameseinstalled government is fighting an 11yearold 
war against the coalition of three guerrilla groups the forces of 
sihanouk the khmer peoples national lieration front of former 
premier son sann and the khmer rouge led by khieu samphan 
both sides say they accept the un peace plan under which the 
united nations would administer the country until elecions are 
held 
on sept 10 six government members and six guerrilla members 
formed the supreme national council but its first meeting held 
last week in bangkok collapsed in bickering over the role of 
sihanouk 
the guerrillas said the former head of state must chair the 
council because he is widely considered the central figure in any 
settlement 
on friday sihanouk urged his guerrilla allies to offer phnom 
penh another council seat if sihanouk joined as chairman 
the guerrilla groups formally agreed to that in a meeting sunday 
and said they wanted a second meeting of the council as soon as 
possible 
hun sen said today he could agree to the proposal only if his 
government received the seat of vice chairman 
both sides have said the next meeting should decide the 
chairmanship appoint a delegation to take cambodias seat at the 
united nations and then work on other issues including stopping 
fighting 
the united nations seat is held by the guerrillas but they are 
ready to transfer it to the council the deadline for the 
presentation of the new credentials is oct 18 
sihanouk who has stayed at his beijing home during recent 
negotiations says he will attend the council meeting after he is 
elected chairman spokesmen in his office said 
thailand was annoyed by the failure of the first council 
meeting and said it will host another meeting only if it is clear 
beforehand there will be agreement 
