jordan said today it would abide by a un 
security council order to cut off air traffic in and out of iraq 
and occupied kuwait but it permitted an iraqi airways flight to 
land 
the regularly scheduled flight from baghdad carried 185 people 
and it was not immediately clear what its cargo hold contained 
but jordanian officials said an initial check of the un 
resolution indicated the arrival was not a violation of the air 
embargo 
the embargo is on cargo shipments only and not passengers 
said one jordanian cabinet minister speaking on condition of 
anonymity according to our initial studying of the resolution 
we understand that it does not bar human traffic 
the security council voted 141 tuesday to prohibit air traffic 
with iraq and kuwait cuba cast the only vote against the 
resolution 
the resolution does not mention passenger planes but says that 
all planes traveling to and from iraq should be checked to make 
sure they are not carrying cargo prohibited by the un trade 
sanctions the resolution prohibits the use of force to stop 
planes but allows for the detention of aircraft 
under certain conditions the council permitted humanitarian 
cargo including food and medical supplies 
an unidentified jordanian transport ministry official was quoted 
by the state news agency petra as saying the civil aviation 
authority and concerned government departments will implement this 
resolution 
the resolution also called on all member states to bar flights 
from their territory to those nations and deny landing rights to 
planes coming from iraq or kuwait 
