sixmonth bills edged down to 777 percent as the discount dipped 1 
basis point to 739 percent yields on oneyear bills were 
unchanged at 785 percent as the discount remained steady at 732 
percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest banks charge one another 
for overnight loans was quoted at 8 percent unchanged from late 
tuesday 
