in an attempt to redeem himself he offers her complete 
servitude and fidelity he tells her that since he tormented her 
for 10 years with his affair he will be her slave for the next 10 
she accepts this pact for a while but soon is undone by the 
recurring jealousy of the other woman she sells her kimonos hires 
a private detective and discovers the sordid secrets of her 
husbands philanderings he bought the other woman underwear gave 
her candy paid for an abortion 
back and forth the couple struggles between saving their 
marriage and resigning themselves to the pain and emptiness before 
them 
he becomes the picture of contrition offering her effusive 
apologies and begging for forgiveness ive thought only of 
myself after the war he confesses 
at times miho seems to have exorcised the ghost of the other 
woman and a semblance of domestic normalcy prevails 
then seemingly from nowhere she blurts out over dinner that 
she wants her husband to forever call her by the name of his 
mistress 
one of their two children who somehow seem oblivious to the 
suffering of their parents tells dad he might as well do as mom 
says 
this pyschological unraveling forms the bulk of this bleak 
story and director oguri said at a news conference after a press 
screening tuesday that he hopes it offers a parable of finding 
faith in the face of adversity 
on the surface it is a crisis of a marriage he said through 
a translator underneath it is a crisis of returning to 
humanity which leads you to the idea of prayer and the 
accomplishment of faith 
the sting of death is marked by its austerity the camera 
rarely leaves the four walls of the home and most sets are drenched 
in soft shades of gray its also a quiet film ambient noise seems 
to have been edited out so the only sounds we hear is the exchange 
of dialogue 
oguri leaves his tale of the broken hearts and souls open 
without resolving if miho and toshio remain together or if they 
part either by death or divorce 
asked to speculate on their future oguri says he would like to 
think they would have become happy 
the 28th new york film festival opened sept 21 with joel and 
ethan coens quirky gangster movie millers crossing the 
17day event features 29 films from 14 countries 
</TEXT>
