chief financial officer of the american newspaper publishers 
association died wednesday he was 51 
fichter was a patient at fair oaks hospital since collapsing 
while jogging near his oakton va home on sept 21 
fichter who had been with the organization for 29 years also 
was treasurer of the anpa foundation and chairman and president of 
anpas credit bureau inc 
toms contribution to newspapers cannot be measured in numbers 
alone said anpa president jerry w friedheim he loved 
newspapers and newspaper people and they greatly appreciated his 
work on their behalf 
