<DOCNO> AP900926-0152 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
alberto moravia one of italys most widely read 
authors who was censored by both fascist and vatican authorities 
died of a heart attack at his home wednesday he was 82 
moravias books many exploring alienation and disillusionment 
with modern society had been translated into all major languages 
and inspired at least eight movies 
in recent years he cut back on his prolific writing schedule 
but made frequent appearances on televison talk shows and 
contributed travel pieces to newspapers an autobiography in the 
form of an interview was due out within weeks 
moravia was ageless with his mental lucidity and constant 
presence in the literary and cultural life of our time said 
valentino bompiani who published moravias works for more than 50 
years 
moravia had been pronounced in good health by a doctor two days 
ago he died seconds after being striken by the heart attack said 
his doctor antonio severini 
moravia and his spanish wife carmen were married in 1986 when 
she was 32 moravias body was taken to the campidoglio or capitol 
hill where senate president giovanni spadolini and rome mayor 
franco carraro were among the mourners funeral services were set 
for friday and burial will be at the moravia family tomb in rome 
another major postwar italian author italo calvino died in 
1985 italys umberto eco has gained attention in the united states 
for several novels including the bestselling the name of the 
rose 
moravias novels often with sexual themes upset fascist 
authorities in the 1930s and roman catholic censors in the 1950s 
la romana about a prostitutes vain search for love in 
postwar rome won moravia world fame it was first published in 
italian in 1947 and its english edition the woman of rome 
sold 1 million copies in the united states and made him the 
bestknown italian writer to many americans 
another major work la ciociara was set in world war ii 
when the allies fought their way from the beaches south of rome on 
the way to liberating the italian capital film director vittorio 
de sica turned the 1957 book into the movie two women with 
sophia loren in an oscarwinning role 
in 1952 the vatican declared all moravias novels and stories 
immoral and placed them on its index of forbidden books the list 
was abolished following the 196365 second vatican council 
born alberto pincherle in rome on nov 28 1907 moravia spent 
much of his childhood suffering from a crippling bone disease he 
often said his approach to life and his writing was largely molded 
by the boredom of his youth 
in 1925 while still on crutches he began his first novel 
the indifferent ones which portrayed the decline of italys 
middleclass in the first years of fascism he paid to have the 
book printed in four languages 
while critics assailed the work it sold quickly 
from october 1934 to may 1935 moravia was in new york lecturing 
at columbia university his encounter with american culture and 
values struck him deeply and fascist authorities began to regard 
moravia with suspicion 
in 1941 the censor seized fancy dress party about a 
grotesque dictator in an imaginary south american country later 
moravia was forbidden to write at all 
in 1941 he married writer elsa morante their marriage ended in 
1962 the next year moravia began living with dacia maraini a 
young author and prominent feminist 
when the germans occupied rome in september 1943 moravia of 
jewish ancestry and listed as subversive by fascist police tried 
to cross the allied lines to naples instead he spent nine months 
hiding with peasants in the mountains 
his wartime experiences were the basis for two women and 
other works 
moravias most prolific years were from 1941 to 1960 during 
which he wrote eight novels and several collections of stories 
including roman tales and new roman tales 
after empty anvas in 1960 moravia concentrated on short 
stories essays film reviews and accounts of his travels 
especially in africa 
in 1970 he shocked the literary world with the novel the two 
of us a dialogue between a sexually hyperactive scriptwriter and 
his genitals some critics described it as moravias surrender to 
alienation 
a ford worker is as alienated as stalins subjects the 
employee as the employer moravia once said vulgarity and 
irreality affect contemporary man 
moravias concern over nuclear arms led him to visit hiroshima 
japan and thrust him into politics in 1984 he was elected to the 
european parliament as a representative of italys independent left 
party 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

