political offspring are meeting mixed success 
as they try to follow in their parents footsteps in this years 
elections 
in new mexico tom udall son of former arizona congressman and 
secretary of the interior stewart udall is running for attorney 
general against a freshman legislator who says he doesnt think the 
udall name is helping his opponent 
in california kathleen brown daughter of one former governor 
and sister of another tells voters im a different shade of 
brown 
in minnesota ted mondale son of former vice president walter 
mondale is challenging a state senator who says the younger 
mondale has no background of any kind other than that hes worked 
in his fathers campaigns 
mondale and his opponent twoterm state sen phyllis mcquaid 
both describe their race as a close one 
you take a name as wellknown in minnesota as mondale its 
clearly very much of a threat ms mcquaid said in a telephone 
interview 
but she added if his name was ted brown no one would take 
the race seriously based on his lack of experience 
her remark recalled another candidates jab at a political 
neophyte nearly three decades ago 
when edward m kennedy ran for senator from massachusetts in 
1962 state attorney general edward j mccormack jr his rival for 
the democratic nomination jeered if your name was simply edward 
moore instead of edward moore kennedy your candidacy would be a 
joke 
