the proposed takeover of mca marks the latest 
chapter in one of hollywoods great success stories the rise of 
mca from jazz band booker to colossus of the entertainment 
industry 
on tuesday matsushita and mca inc said they were in talks for 
a possible merger valued at about 7 billion 
mcas transformation was stagemanaged over the companys 
65year history by a chicago eye doctor the late jules stein and 
a onetime movie usher from cleveland lew wasserman 
stein laid the groundwork for mcas dominance of the band 
business and emergence as the top agency for movie talent 
wasserman pushed the corporation into television and movie 
production tourist attractions and a myriad of enterprises 
though he deals in billions and is the confidant of presidents 
particularly former client ronald reagan wasserman has run the mca 
empire with a silken glove he eschews interviews and 
selfpromotion his biography in the motion picture almanac lists 
only his title as mca chairman 
until 1959 mca was known principally as the octopus because of 
its farreaching influence as a talent agency then the company 
took a giant step buying the venerable faltering universal 
pictures the justice department forced mca to exit the agency 
business or face antitrust charges 
universal pictures had been created by carl laemmle known as 
uncle carl because of his penchant for hiring relatives he was a 
pintsized scrapper who left the clothing business in oshkosh 
neb to open a nickelodeon in chicago in 1906 he soon built a 
theater chain then launched his own production company 
challenging the motion picture trust which demanded royalties for 
use of thomas edisons inventions 
the star system was started in 1910 when laemmle lured florence 
lawrence away from biograph with a salary of 200 a week he also 
hired little mary pickford in 1912 laemmle gathered in other 
independent companies to form universal pictures 
i hope im not making a mistake going out there said 
laemmle in a rare moment of selfdoubt as he moved his filmmaking 
to california he paid 165000 for a ranch on the north side of 
