young to sign the paychecks universal flourished in the 1920s with 
such stars as lon chaney and mae murray and directors such as john 
ford and erich von stroheim 
the studio specialized in westerns and horror classics included 
chaneys silent the hunchback of notre dame and the phantom 
of the opera and the talkies dracula and frankenstein 
