said such speculation is premature and not well founded 
the pan am shuttle flies between new york and washington dc 
and new york and boston thomas plaskett chairman of pan am said 
last week that he expected to sell the shuttle by the end of the 
year although he declined to identify potential buyers 
america west tried last year to buy the trump shuttle which 
also serves the new yorkbostonwashington corridor but was unable 
to come up with the necessary financing 
airbus industrie a european aerospace consortium said last 
week that it and general electric co which makes engines for its 
jets had arranged for a 500 million loan for northwest airlines 
as part of a deal in which northwest would by 75 airbus jets 
alan boyd chairman of airbus north america said airbus would 
not loan any money to america west 
