<TEXT>
newsweek and times mirror magazines are teaming 
up to offer advertisers package deals involving combinations of 
their magazines and affiliated newspapers television stations and 
cable tv systems 
the sponsors said the program was a first for separately owned 
consumer magazine publishers 
companies that publish several magazine titles such as time 
warner inc and hearst corp have frequently sold packages 
involving space in combinations of their own magazines newspapers 
or radio and tv stations 
but newsweek which is owned by washington post co and the 
times mirror inc subsidiary said their program is the first 
marketing package involving consumer magazines to be offered by 
companies independent of each other 
it is being called the newsweektime mirror advantage program 
media analysts and the programs supporters say it should help 
newsweek compete more effectively against the newsweeklies time and 
us news amp world report in the scramble for advertising revenue 
many advertising experts felt newsweek was placed at a 
disadvantage when time magazine co launched an incentive plan more 
than a year ago involving its magazines which includes time 
people sports illustrated life and fortune 
the advantage plan gives discounts to advertisers who meet 
certain minimum spending criteria in newsweek and at least four of 
the 10 times mirror titles and agree to boost their spending in 
those magazines by 20 percent 
the companies said the 11 magazines in the program have a 
combined circulation of 125 million led by 31 million for 
newsweek and can reach some key audiences 
for example they said the magazines reach 28 million men or 33 
percent of the adult men in the united states 
the times mirror titles in the program are field amp stream golf 
magazine home mechanix outdoor life popular science salt water 
sportsman ski magazine skiing the sporting news and yachting 
in addition to the discount plan the companies plan to publish 
special supplements that will appear in combinations of the 
magazines 
a supplement called travels for instance will be published 
next spring in golf ski yachting and the portion of newsweek that 
goes to business executives another supplement called your 
home will be published in the fall of 1991 with the full run of 
newsweek home mechanix and popular science 
the program will also enable advertisers to buy multimedia 
packages that could include combinations of magazines and 
newspapers owned by the parents of the magazines such as the 
washington post los angeles times newsday the baltimore sun and 
the hartford conn courant 
the multimedia packages could also include commercial time on 
the parent companies eight tv stations and their cable tv systems 
the companies will also offer to create programs for magazine 
advertisers that can include event sponsorship outdoor advertising 
and store displays 
peter eldredge publisher of newsweek said newsweek hopes to 
attrac more advertising from companies that deal in sporting 
goods insurance and home improvement that are heavy spenders in 
times mirror magazines 
at the same time he said times mirror may get more revenue from 
advertising categories represented heavily in newsweek such as 
automotive business equipment airline and liquor 
james kopper executive vice president at times mirror 
magazines said his company teamed up with newsweek because of the 
quality of the magazine and the long corporate relationship between 
their parent companies the washington post and los angeles times 
for instance have operated a news service since 1963 
he said in a telephone interview that he expects a 
considerable incremental benefit to result for both magazine 
operations as a result of the program 
the entire marketing community has been screaming for 
multimedia buys this is a strategic alliance that enables us to 
accomplish what the marketplace has been asking for he said 
</TEXT>
