<TEXT>
mca inc stockholders filed a classaction 
lawsuit wednesday in an attempt to open the bidding on a possible 
buyout of the entertainment conglomerate by matsushita electric 
industrial co 
the superior court lawsuit seeks a court order to prevent mca 
and its board of directors from limiting talks to the japanese 
firm a leader in the production of stereos televisions and tape 
players 
an attorney for the shareholders said his clients arent sure if 
any other firms are interested in mca but allan schulman said the 
plaintiffs felt an open bidding process might attract a more 
lucrative offer 
the wall street journal has reported that matsushita is offering 
70 to 80 a share for mca stock or 67 billion to 75 billion 
for the firm 
roger armstrong mcas vice president for publicity said he had 
not seen the lawsuit and could not comment other mca officials 
could not be reached wednesday night 
if completed the acquisition would combine matsushitas 
dominance in electronics hardware with mcas broad strength in 
movie record and television production matsushitas product lines 
include technics panasonic and quasar 
mcas holdings include universal studios mca records universal 
television the producer of the murder she wrote series as 
well as mcauniversal home video a theme park franchise a cable 
tv unit a publishing group a concert and sports merchandising 
arm movie theaters and a 49 percent share in movie theater chain 
cineplex odeon 
schulman said more than 73 million shares of mca stock have been 
issued and public stockholders number in the thousands although 
he could not provide an exact figure 
both matsushita and mca have remained tightlipped about the 
talks matsushita has said only that mca is one of several 
companies with which it is talking mca confirmed in a prepared 
statement that it is in discussions with a major international 
company regarding a possible acquisition but would say no more 
word of the talks tuesday sent stock soaring 1950 to 5400 
per share on wednesday stock rose another 725 to 6125 
mcas 1989 revenues were 34 billion with income of 191 
million matsushita reported 1989 sales of 444 billion 
